The purpose of the Animal Waste Technology Fund is to provide financial assistance to individuals and business enterprises that:
Conduct research or develop technologies that are intended to reduce the amount of nutrients in animal waste;
Alter the composition of animal waste;
Develop alternative animal waste management strategies; or
Use animal waste in a production process.

The Fund consists of:
Money appropriated in the State budget to the Fund;
Any other money from any other source accepted for the benefit of the Fund;
Any investment earnings of the Fund;
Repayments of principal and interest from loans made from the Fund;
Income from equity investments that the State Treasurer makes from the Fund;
Proceeds from the sale, disposition, lease, or rental by the Department of collateral related to any financing provided by the Department under this subtitle; and
Application or other fees paid to the Department in connection with the processing of requests for assistance.
